article.headline: Mississippi St. 73, New Orleans 54
article.story:
NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Tan White had 20 points and 10 rebounds to
lead Mississippi State to a 73-54 victory over New Orleans in the
Lady Bulldogs' final non-conference game of the season Tuesday.

Seneca Anderson and Blessing Chekwa each had 11 points for the
Lady Bulldogs (9-11), who shot 49 percent from the floor.

Jasmine Smiri scored 13 points and Susan Griffee had 11 points
for New Orleans, which made only 32 percent of its shots.

White was 9-for-15 from the floor for Mississippi State and
Chekwa and Anderson combined to shoot 10-for-17.
